		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>I had two thoughts here:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<UL>
<LI>What if we&nbsp;had a minimum level cap of say level 2-10 for bazaar entrance, it might cut down on the plat sellers?&nbsp; If the plat sellers don't know how to play the game maybe it would be that much more of a discouragement?&nbsp; I mean honestly anything to help get rid of them I am sure none of us would&nbsp;complain about it would we?</LI></UL>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<UL>
<LI>Also SWG bazaar settings allow you to upload your merchandise, set the prices, set it to fixed price sale or set it to auction bidding with a cap of 20k I think (would have to tweak this part obviously for those out there doing the new 300k price tagging).</LI></UL>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So you could upload your items, set the prices and variables and go back to playing.</DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							~ New Subliminal Message ~ Don't fear change in EQ...If something has to change to draw new players from WoW, DDO, CoH/V then suck it up and live with it.
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
