		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			A level limit wouldn't do much.<br><br>On the other hand, I do like the idea of setting up one area of the bazaar (add a new node maybe?) as an auction house. You get on a pedastal in the area and go in 'auction' mode. You can then set what you want to auction, a starting bid and a minimum bid, minimum increment, and how long the auction is good for. (hourly increments, up to 24 hours).<br><br>Bidders cna open a bidding window, see what is listed and set their max bid (like e-bay).<br><br>As long as the auctioner is on the pedastal, the auction is considered 'open' and people can bid.<br><br>When the auction time is done, regardless if either person is online, emails are sent to the auctioner and the winning bidder saying who won and for what price. It is then up to those two players to get together and make the actual exchange.<br><br>(To make things easier though, it might be nice if either the email system could be expanded to send item's/plat via email, or that a barterer/seller in the bazaar could flag an item specifically for someone, so they can then go into barter/buyer mode and say "I am buying X from PlayerY" or say "I am selling X to PlayerY")<br><br>It would be an interesting idea to develop in any case.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Saroc, L70 Dwarf Cleric; Member of Heroes 
Trilium, L52 Druid
Taeolas, L39 Ranger

Luclin server.
