			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=156513#M156513">11</a> of 17
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 203 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I have to disagree on the offline trading, though I once would have agreed, and I may have even posted a request for that in the past.</P>
<P>The appeal of the bazaar to me is the human element.&nbsp; Financial games have always been poor due due to their </P>
<P>pre-programmed, or worse completely random, nature, and this is (like it or not) a financial sub-element of Everquest with a great deal of complexity.&nbsp; The EQ bazaar is more than just buying and selling; it is a place that reveals the character of the players.&nbsp; There you have the clueless, the desperate, and the greedy.&nbsp; You have those that are honorably proud of always having the lowest price, and those who would sell their grandmother's liver if it would turn a plat or two.&nbsp; Then there are those who never leave, and those who just want to get their business done and get out.&nbsp; The Bazaar is a place full of fads and bargain hunting.&nbsp; Today you can't find a good DS aug to save your life; but tomorrow there will be a glut on the market.&nbsp; It's a place that feels LIVED IN.&nbsp; Characters and pets are scattered all over the place, standing around talking for hours or days at a time.</P>
<P>The bazaar has rhythms based on time of day, day of week, and state of the server.&nbsp; POK is a stepping stone to many destinations, while the bazaar IS a destination.&nbsp; We've all read the threads on how POK ruined the game, but we all use it.&nbsp; Frankly, doing away with the bazaar and replacing it with classified ads would remove the most social area of the game.&nbsp; Yes POK is social, too, but it seems like players come and go too quickly to "stick".&nbsp; In the bazaar you will find people hanging out for hours...&nbsp; It's a place where people sit all day while doing housework so that they can sit down and rest a few minutes each hour and catch up on the conversation.</P>
<P>The other day somehow a "thing" got started and everyone started parking their pets in the Red 'porter room.&nbsp; there must have been 60 or 70 pets there.&nbsp; Everyone was chatting about it for hours wondering how it got started, and why.</P>
<P>As someone who has spent countless hours in the bazaar, I would caution against removing the human element.&nbsp; There are many other major changes in the Bazaar that I would love, but not that one.&nbsp; Let's give the craziest place in Norrath a double whammy of Valium and Prozak?&nbsp; Anti-anxiety and anti-depressant medicine all at once?</P>
<P>Where would be the fun in that?&nbsp; I prefer the bazaar just a little bit crazy...</P>
<P><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_woman-mad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_man-mad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_robot-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>	
		</td></tr>
