		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<br><blockquote><hr>PebblePuppy wrote:<br><P>I have to disagree on the offline trading, though I once would have agreed, and I may have even posted a request for that in the past.</P><P>The appeal of the bazaar to me is the human element.  Financial games have always been poor due due to their </P><P>pre-programmed, or worse completely random, nature, and this is (like it or not) a financial sub-element of Everquest with a great deal of complexity.  The EQ bazaar is more than just buying and selling; it is a place that reveals the character of the players.  There you have the clueless, the desperate, and the greedy.  You have those that are honorably proud of always having the lowest price, and those who would sell their grandmother's liver if it would turn a plat or two.  Then there are those who never leave, and those who just want to get their business done and get out.  The Bazaar is a place full of fads and bargain hunting.  Today you can't find a good DS aug to save your life; but tomorrow there will be a glut on the market.  It's a place that feels LIVED IN.  Characters and pets are scattered all over the place, standing around talking for hours or days at a time.</P><P>The bazaar has rhythms based on time of day, day of week, and state of the server.  POK is a stepping stone to many destinations, while the bazaar IS a destination.  We've all read the threads on how POK ruined the game, but we all use it.  Frankly, doing away with the bazaar and replacing it with classified ads would remove the most social area of the game.  Yes POK is social, too, but it seems like players come and go too quickly to "stick".  In the bazaar you will find people hanging out for hours...  It's a place where people sit all day while doing housework so that they can sit down and rest a few minutes each hour and catch up on the conversation.</P><P>The other day somehow a "thing" got started and everyone started parking their pets in the Red 'porter room.  there must have been 60 or 70 pets there.  Everyone was chatting about it for hours wondering how it got started, and why.</P><P>As someone who has spent countless hours in the bazaar, I would caution against removing the human element.  There are many other major changes in the Bazaar that I would love, but not that one.  Let's give the craziest place in Norrath a double whammy of Valium and Prozak?  Anti-anxiety and anti-depressant medicine all at once?</P><P>Where would be the fun in that?  I prefer the bazaar just a little bit crazy...</P><P><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_woman-mad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_man-mad.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_robot-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P><br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br><br>WELL SAID!!!  4 stars ****<br><br>I just wish they would bing back the FEEL of the old bazaar.  Where are the over head tarps?  Where is the bar?? Where are the merchant tables and barrols and boxes?<br><br>The bazaar is still fun...but GOD i wish they would just add some of the old eye candy to the new bazaar.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
