Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=156662#M156662">14</a> of 17
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 167 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I agree with PebblePuppy and Mchaos.&nbsp; The bazaar should be a crazy jumble of sights and sounds...&nbsp; just like a real bazaar.&nbsp; A place where shops are tucked away in little corners and animals, wares, and services are openly sold anywhere there is a space to be had.&nbsp; I've traveled around the world and I've seen many markets and bazaars.&nbsp; The shopping mall implementation of the current EQ bazaar isn't the true vision of a bazaar and should be changed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Maybe there could be more than one market?&nbsp; You could have ritzy markets where snobbish vendors look you up and down when you approach them, and then crazy open-air markets where animal drawn carts and peasants are dominant.&nbsp; Where are the street rats, drunks, and prostitutes?&nbsp; He he.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What I want to see is confusion and bursting energy.&nbsp; When I zone into the bazaar I want to hear multitudes shouting out their bargains, vendor stands and little tents plucked down anywhere, and some excitement to the atmosphere.&nbsp; Yeah, I'm just like many who don't visit the bazaar very often.&nbsp; I basically go in and quickly go out.&nbsp; But I've asked myself why and the reason for me is that it isn't exciting.&nbsp; There isn't any immersion to it and I don't feel compelled to go.&nbsp; The Nexus isn't bustling anymore either.&nbsp; Want to make the game more social?&nbsp; More exciting?&nbsp; Make it a little crazy in the bazaar and then look at some of the other places where it is too organized and the paths are linear.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Just my two cents.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SS</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
