<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=156950#M156950">17</a> of 17
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 102 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
digitalrexxus wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I'd like to see a price-search and compare feature, too, and be able to tie in a sound when someone undercuts my prices.&nbsp; I've actually seen people raise prices back up and then drop them again as soon as you walk away from the machine or become obviously afk&nbsp;- this would stop such sniping.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>I don't think it is a good idea to use alerts/watches in the bazaar. The /bazaar tool is quite useful for manual searches, but I think that alerts would be crossing a line and the first&nbsp;of a&nbsp;"slippery-slope" series of requests for added functionality from the community. Sure, you may be happy with the alerts, but some will want them to trigger macros, and at that point there will be debate about expanding the functionality within macros... If that sounds ridiculous, think about what you might have said if you were told about the /bazaar search back in the EC tunnel days pre-Luclin.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Additionally, automating more of the process would hurt the bazaar savvy by making it easier for the less active trader which would in turn reduce the amount of people who make money by buying and selling. Sounds useless anyways, right? Well, everyone is good at something, and bazaar resellers allow those who farm gear to spend more time farming and less time selling. Everyone sticks to what they are good at and the market operates at greater efficiency than if everyone sold what they farmed themselves, plus this would prevent some people (such as myself) who are poor at farming good gear from making any in-game income. This style of earning platinum has already been hurt by /barter, at least if you do not have two accounts so you may operate both a buyer and trader.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1069548" target=new resize="true"><img src="http://i22.photobucket.com/albums/b319/vaedian/vaedian_75x75_named.jpg"></a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1153949" target=new resize="true"><img src="http://i22.photobucket.com/albums/b319/vaedian/lixea_75x75_named.jpg"></a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1236981" target=new resize="true"><img src="http://i22.photobucket.com/albums/b319/vaedian/davven_75x75_named.jpg"></a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1264108" target=new resize="true"><img src="http://i22.photobucket.com/albums/b319/vaedian/tisha_75x75_named.jpg"></a><br>What the **HALFLING**? Because smurfs just aren't RP.
							</div>
								
